{"findings":[{"capability_id":"UPLOAD_TYPE_MAGIC","issue":"Upload validation relies only on the filename extension and does not verify the declared MIME type, magic bytes, or file size before saving.","evidence_span":"app.py: def upload(filename: str, content_type: str, file_bytes: bytes) -> dict:
    if filename.endswith((".png", ".jpg")):
        save(str(UPLOAD_ROOT / filename), file_bytes)","recommended_fix":"Validate extension, declared MIME type, file signature/magic bytes, and size together before accepting the upload; reject files that fail any check."},{"capability_id":"UPLOAD_PATH_ISOLATION","issue":"The upload handler writes a user-controlled filename directly under a public upload directory, allowing unsafe path construction and lack of server-side object naming.","evidence_span":"app.py: UPLOAD_ROOT = Path("/public/uploads")
