        save(str(UPLOAD_ROOT / filename), file_bytes)
config.yaml: upload_storage: /public/uploads","recommended_fix":"Generate server-side random filenames or object IDs, normalize and constrain paths, and store uploads outside public executable roots; serve files through controlled download handlers."},{"capability_id":"UPLOAD_AUDIT_RETENTION","issue":"Audit retention is unset and the upload/download handlers do not record audit events for upload activity.","evidence_span":"config.yaml: audit_log_retention_days:
app.py: def upload(filename: str, content_type: str, file_bytes: bytes) -> dict:
    if filename.endswith((".png", ".jpg")):
